HEADWORD: Delftware
<hw>Delft"ware`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Pottery made at the city of <city><etsep>Delft</etsep></city> in
Holland; hence:</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Earthenware made in imitation of
the above; any glazed earthenware made for table use, and the
like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

